<html lang="en" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
	<title>ACLU Email</title>
	<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" />
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
	<meta name="color-scheme" content="light dark" />
	<meta name="supported-color-schemes" content="light dark" />
	{% include "partials/styles.html" %}
</head>
<body>
	{% include "partials/preheader.njk" %}
	<table role="presentation" align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="email-wrapper" width="{{theme.sizing.wrapper}}">
		<tbody>
			{% include "partials/logo.njk" %}
			<tr>
				<td class="email-content" style="color: {{theme.colors.default.black}}; font-family: Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-size: {{theme.typography.body}}; line-height: 22px; padding: 15px 0px 20px 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid #d4d4d4" valign="top">
					{% include "partials/salutation.njk" %}

					<p>Any template you create will use <code>blank</code> layout template by default. That template will only have the doctype. You will need to add the head/body code. This gives you as much control over the template without relying on our base styles.</p>

					<blockquote style="border-left: 3px solid #f3ef07; padding-left: 10px;margin-left:15px;">
						<p>
							<strong>&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd"&gt;</strong>
						</p>
					</blockquote>

					<p>You can use our pre-existing pre-header by include this snipper below.</p>

					<blockquote style="border-left: 3px solid #f3ef07; padding-left: 10px;margin-left:15px;">
						<p>
							<strong>{% raw %}{% include "partials/preheader.njk" %}{% endraw %}</strong>
						</p>
					</blockquote>

					<p>These are the HTML codes you can use to replace curly quotes (') and apostrophes(â€œ).</p>

					<ol>
						<li>Use the code <span class="highlight">&#38;#39&#59;</span> or <span class="highlight">&amp;apos&semi;</span> to output <span class="highlight">&apos;</span>. Or you can just use your keyboard.</li>

						<li>Use the code <span class="highlight">&#38;#34&#59;</span> or <span class="highlight">&amp;quot&semi;</span> to output <span class="highlight">&quot;</span>. Or you can just use your keyboard.</li>
					</ol>

					<p><strong>Anthony Romero<br/>
					Pronouns: He, him, his<br />
					ACLU Executive Director</strong></p>
				</td>
			</tr>
			{% include "partials/footer.njk" %}
		</tbody>
	</table>
</body>
</html>